This is the moment where The Combine stops being a software-generating tool and becomes an operating system for work, capable of producing plans, systems, and physical-world outputs.

üî• Key Insights
1. The PM must set architect_domain

The PM now outputs something like:

"architect_domain": "software"


or:

"architect_domain": "physical"


or:

"architect_domain": "hybrid"


This allows the Architect role to completely change "world models" depending on the type of work.

2. Software vs Physical vs Hybrid Architecture

This was the breakthrough:

üß© Software Architecture

We control fabrication (code ‚Üí build ‚Üí deploy ‚Üí operate).
The entire pipeline is internal to The Combine.

üåø Physical Architecture

We design, but humans (or the physical world) execute the plans.
The Combine is an advisor, not the builder.

ü§ñ Hybrid Architecture

We design AND fabricate via machines (CNC, robotic systems, 3D printing, IoT).

This sets the stage for The Combine to eventually become a cyber-physical system designer and maker.

